com.tsgrp.migration.event.existencecheck

Interface ExistenceCheck


  • public interface ExistenceCheck
    This interface describes a class uesd to check for existence in the target. Different logic is required if the piece of content does exist in the target. Implementing classes will be called via the abstract migration target. existencecheck was created using IntelliJ IDEA.

    • Method Detail

      • checkExistence

        boolean checkExistence(MigrationTarget target,
                       MigrationNode node)
        Determine whether the migrationnode exists in the target. Return true if it does, false if it does not.
        Parameters:
        target - The migration target used in the migration
        node - the node that is being migrated
        resultLog - the result log
        Returns:
        true iff the rest of the existence checkers should continue. Instead of returning true the existence checkers sets an attribute on the migration node.

      • supportsType

        boolean supportsType(MigrationTarget target,
                     java.lang.String type)
        Determines whether the node exists in the target.
        Parameters:
        type - the type we are checking
        target - the migration target we are migrating to.
        Returns:
        true iff this existence check implementation supports the specified type.
